overturn the decision that resulted from roe vs wade 
the high court is scheduled to hear arguments in webster vs 
reproductive health services on april 26 the case involves a 
federal appeals court ruling that struck down key provisions of a 
missouri antiabortion law declaring that human life begins at 
conception 
last september blackmun told law students at the university of 
arkansas theres a very distinct possibility that roe vs wade 
will be overturned by the high court because you can count the 
votes 
the associate justice said saturday night he had been getting 
voluminous mail on the subject with some people branding him 
morally rotten and responsible for the deaths of more babies 
in the history of world 
asked about his philosophy of law blackmun said i think we 
need some compassion in judgments let me just leave my 
constitutional philosophy at that 
the symposium marked the 50th anniversary of the late william o 
douglas appointment to the high court douglas served longer than 
any other justice in us history the symposium also came on the 
19th anniversary of blackmuns appointment they were on the bench 
together for five years 
douglas was an extremely talented person with love of the 
environment veneration of the first amendment ease of writing 
lack of pomposity blackmun said 
i saw douglas as a person with whom i had to get along 
blackmun added he put me on the defensive because of his 
accomplishments 
blackmun said his constitutional philosophy has developed in his 
years on the court but still holds the opinions he held before his 
appointment 
if one reads my opinions in the us court of appeals i 
think youll find i havent changed though i suppose ive 
changed in the sense that ive tried to develop a constitutional 
philosophy he said 
</TEXT>
