18nation organization for a sixyear term he previously was the 
councils fisheries officer and statistician 
the council was set up in 1902 to carry out marine and fishery 
science and advise european nations on fish stocks quotas and 
marine pollution 
we try to keep out of politics and fisheries management 
anderson said but were sometimes the source of controversy 
he said the councils greatest challenge was making people 
recognize their responsibility for common resources 
prior to the mid1970s when countries extended their national 
jurisdictions to 200 miles there was virtual anarchy among fishing 
nations anderson said nothing changed until fish stocks were 
decimated he said 
anderson said the north sea where cod and haddock are severely 
depleted was the most overfished ocean in europe he said fishing 
in north sea waters should be cut by 80 percent to replenish stocks 
to a sufficient level 
