percent of their income for rent and utilities rose from 44 percent 
in 1978 to 55 percent in 1985 
among poor owners the proportion rose from 31 percent to 38 
percent 
half of all poor renting households paid at least 266 a month 
in 1985 up from the 1978 figure of 229 
