<TEXT>
luxembourg a nation smaller than the state of 
rhode island marks its 150th anniversary tuesday determined to 
survive among the great powers that spawned its independence 
a speck on the world map tucked between france west germany 
and belgium the grand duchy has used its position on the 
crossroads of europes main cultures to maintain one of the highest 
standards of living in the world 
dont mix us up with countries that are even smaller than 
ours said lex roth a government spokesman 
luxembourg with a population of 372000 became independent of 
the netherlands under the 1839 treaty of london signed by the 
european powers 
since then its fate has been determined by close cooperation 
with its neighbors an inevitable option for a nation that covers 
only 999 square miles rhode island is 1214 square miles 
it is essential a small state like us can survive and develop 
by keeping its independence only within great frameworks prime 
minister jacques santer who heads a centerleft coalition 
government said recently 
luxembourg is a founding member of the north atlantic treaty 
organization and an ardent member of the european economic 
community 
it is home for a number of eec institutions including the 
european investment bank and the european court of justice 
luxembourg license plates display the eec flag of 12 gold stars in 
a field of royal blue 
tuesdays independence celebrations will be attended by foreign 
dignitaries from many nations including west germany britain the 
soviet union and france 
in recent decades luxembourg has become a financial center the 
city of luxembourg with a population of 75000 has more than 100 
banks from around the world and the banking industry employs 10 
percent of the work force and accounts for a quarter of the 
national income 
the financial institutions have helped keep unemployment at 
about 15 percent by far the lowest in the 12nation eec 
immigrants account for 27 percent of the population the highest 
in the eec 
problems involving immigrants do exist roth said but without 
the violence that mars coexistence in many other european nations 
although they have no voting rights our portuguese and italian 
fellow citizens have all the same social rights as luxembourgers 
he said 
to improve integration a relaxed naturalization process in 
recent years has made it easier for immigrants to gain citizenship 
language poses a problem for foreigners from southern europe 
roth said most luxembourgers speak german and french along with 
luxembourgish a german dialect 
but roth added were a good blend the french are more 
impulsive the germans more heavyhanded giving luxembourgers 
balance and patience 
</TEXT>
