the house approved on monday a bill to remove 
remaining federal price controls on natural gas 
the measure passed and sent to the senate by voice vote 
removes all price controls at the wellhead however the federal 
energy regulatory commission would retain the power to regulate 
rates charged by interstate natural gas pipelines and states would 
retain their regulatory powers over consumer prices 
most gas from wells drilled after the enactment of the 1978 
natural gas policy act has been decontrolled for several years the 
new legislation would gradually remove controls from old gas 
that from wells predating the 1978 act 
