<TEXT>
a federal bankruptcy judge granted a oneweek 
extention today to eastern airlines and its creditors to devise 
plans for a sale or restructuring but he warned delays were 
devouring the strikecrippled carrier 
the order by judge burton lifland came as lawyers for pilots and 
eastern confirmed the existence of another possible bidder besides 
the three previously known exbaseball boss peter ueberroth 
hotelier jay pritzker and takeover investor carl icahn but the 
lawyers wouldnt identify the fourth bidder 
directors of easterns parent texas air corp meanwhile said 
they have decided it should no longer pursue the sale of eastern 
but will consider selling a substantial part of the companys 
assets to pay its debts 
the texas air boards statement essentially approved eastern 
managements decision last wednesday after a deal with ueberroth 
fell through to reduce eastern to about 60 percent of its 
prestrike size 
as time goes by there are fewer alternatives to explore 
lifland told a manhattan courtroom crammed with about 50 uniformed 
pilots and lawyers for texas air creditors and the striking unions 
this airline is hemorrhaging he said it is not tolerable 
that this process be so lengthy that the parties have nothing left 
to consider 
burton had called a hearing today requesting that management 
creditors and the unions show cause why he shouldnt put the entire 
airline up for auction including assets owned by eastern before 
texas air bought it three years ago 
we are not here selling a used car at a foreclosure sale 
creditors committee attorney joel zweibel told the judge we are 
selling a complicated business 
at the urging of zweibel and lawyers for eastern management 
lifland gave them one more week to negotiate and review possible 
options for the miamibased airline one of the nations largest 
and most unprofitable he set a new hearing for 11 am next monday 
lifland granted the delay over the objection of attorneys for 
the unions and a dissident creditor who sought the hearing they 
have been pushing for more aggressive court action to get eastern 
flying again either through a sale or the appointment of an 
outsider to run the airline eastern management has said it wants 
to restructure into a much smaller operation 
eastern workers have been on strike since march 4 charging 
texas air boss frank lorenzo has butchered it and plotted to 
destroy their unions by transferring valuable assets to sister 
carrier continental airlines 
lorenzo put eastern into bankruptcy court refuge march 9 and 
sought a buyer ueberroth the former baseball commissioner and 
olympics organizer nearly completed a 464 million deal to buy 
eastern but the sale collapsed 
however sources familiar with the eastern situation have said 
ueberroth remains interested in making a new offer pritzker owner 
of the hyatt hotel chain and icahn chairman of trans world 
airlines also have been lurking in the background as possible 
buyers 
after the lifland hearing today pilots union attorney bruce 
simon and eastern attorney harvey miller told reporters there was a 
fourth bidder 
in a statement issued today lorenzo was quoted as saying the 
texas air board believes a sale of eastern is not in texas air or 
easterns best interests or in the best interests of easterns 
creditors 
the board made the decision at a meeting this morning and its 
vote was unrelated to liflands action today texas air spokesman 
art kent said from the companys headquarters in houston 
the statement said in order to resolve promptly the eastern 
situation texas air had been willing to agree to a quick sale 
even at a price which did not nearly reflect easterns net asset 
value and had selected the prospective buyer the group led by 
peter ueberroth who it believed was most likely to be able to 
consummate a transaction promptly 
with the collapse of those efforts because of totally 
unreasonable and unworkable union demands texas air has determined 
that further sale efforts are unlikely to be successful and in 
fact would be counterproductive 
pritzker resurfaced friday with a 500 million proposal to buy 
eastern which his representatives presented to the 15member 
committee of easterns major creditors sources close to the 
situation said ueberroth remained interested in reviving his bid 
and icahn the owner and chairman of trans world airlines inc 
talked to union officials this weekend about a possible deal said 
the sources who spoke on condition of anonymity 
lawyers representing eastern and its unions also met during the 
weekend but little of significance was said to have emerged from 
