holly farms corp trying to block a 115 
billion takeover by a rival poultry processor said monday it 
failed to convince its stockholders to approve a merger holly 
managers proposed with conagra inc and would abandon the idea 
holly farms said a preliminary count showed that only 325 
percent of its stock was voted in favor of the merger with conagra 
and 478 percent against it the tally was taken friday with a 
twothirds affirmative vote required 
ted bailey a holly farms vice president said holly notified 
conagra on monday that the merger was off 
holly farms directors announced the proposed merger with omaha 
nebbased conagra last november to ward off a takeover by tyson 
foods inc of springdale ark 
they had to have a twothirds vote and they didnt even get 
onethird jim blair general counsel for tyson said of the 
shareholder voting i would hope the holly board would start 
paying a little attention to the wishes of their shareholders i 
think this is a mandate to take our deal 
the merger agreement included a provision aimed at allowing 
conagra to purchase key holly assets in the event the merger 
failed the assetoption agreement remains in effect though it 
has been temporarily blocked by delaware chancery court on a 
challenge by tyson bailey said 
the court also blocked another provision of the merger proposal 
requiring holly farms to pay conagra 15 million plus expenses if 
the deal failed 
walt casey a conagra vice president said his companys 
expenses for the merger attempt total 5 million 
casey said conagra still is interested in holly farms but he 
declined to say if his company will make a higher offer to counter 
tyson 
tyson is offering holly stockholders 6350 a share in cash for 
their 181 million shares 
the offer is contingent however on removal of the assetoption 
agreement between conagra and holly farms 
the conagra merger which would have made holly farms a conagra 
subsidiary called for a 11 billion stock swap worth about 61 a 
share 
the board will be meeting and reviewing alternatives available 
to shareolders and will be asking that the shareholders do nothing 
in respect to their stock until they hear from the board bailey 
said 
tyson foods is the nations largest poultry processor and holly 
farms a diversified company is heavily involved in fresh poultry 
sales conagra is one of the largest food companies in the country 
with revenues of 94 billion last year 
the assetoption agreement between conagra and holly farms 
allows conagra to purchase about onethird of hollys assets at 
prices already negotiated if the memphis company is bought by 
anyone else within the next nine months 
tyson contends the asset agreement was an illegal attempt to 
make holly farms unattractive to any buyer other than conagra 
the delaware judge hearing tysons suit has blocked any 
execution of the asset agreement until the legal disputes 
surrounding it are settled 
