<TEXT>
the nuclear regulatory commission on monday 
gave a pennsylvania nuclear plant permission to resume operations 
two years after it was shut down because 33 control room operators 
slept on the job or neglected their duties 
the nrc voted 30 to lift an order that had kept the peach 
bottom nuclear plant closed since march 31 1987 when the 
commission said its continued operation posed a threat to the 
health and safety of the public 
in granting permission to restart the facility the commission 
nevertheless warned the plant operator against complacency we 
will be watching you very closely said nrc chairman lando zech 
plant officials must complete a checklist of technical items 
before bringing the plant to full power which will take several 
months and be scrutinized by nrc inspectors 
the vote followed a presentation by philadelphia electric co 
the plant operator which said it had undergone radical changes 
since the nrc issued its order following a tip about the sleeping 
that prompted an investigation 
the changes successfully addressed the root causes of the 
problem the nrc staff said in recommending that the commission 
permit the plant to restart 
those problems had included a lax peach bottom culture in 
which plant problems either were ignored or unnoticed by top 
managers the staff said 
it would at least appear to me that management before the 
shutdown either was not aware of conditions or if they were aware 
of it they condoned it zech said before the vote 
the operators must never again betray the special trust and 
countenance of the public zech said we will be watching you 
very closely 
nrc commissioner james curtis was out of the country and missed 
the vote commissioner kenneth rogers did not vote because he once 
served on the philadelphia electric board the nrc said 
the shutdown cost the company about 250 million in plant 
modifications purchases of replacement power and its share of a 
125 million fine the largest in nrc history 
many of the problems at peach bottom occured on the overnight 
or graveyard shift 
on at least two occasions according to nrc testimony in 1987 
three of the four control room employees responsible for running 
the plant were asleep at the same time another time several of 
the operators were found huddled around a personal computer playing 
video games 
of 39 control room operators now at the plant 24 were there at 
the time of the shutdown and all have been retrained to end 
catnaps by operators plant officials also replaced comfortable 
highbacked chairs in the control room with lowbacked models 
in another development meanwhile zech indicated the committee 
would vote thursday on awarding a fullpower license to the 
shoreham nuclear plant on long island after hearing the nrc staff 
report that the 55 billion reactor is safe and ready to operate 
all indications are that the fullpower license will be awarded 
but whether it will ever be used is doubtful the long island 
lighting co is one step away from selling the plant to new york 
state for 1 in exchange for a decade of annual rate increases of 
up to 5 percent the state would then decommission and dismantle 
the plant 
lilcos board of directors is recommending that shareholders 
approve the plan to shut the plant the final step to ratifying the 
settlement is a vote by lilco shareholders on or before june 15 in 
the meantime lilco has agreed not to operate the plant even if it 
receives a 25 percent or fullpower license before then 
shoreham which was completed in 1984 13 years behind schedule 
received a lowpower testing license in 1985 but lilco was 
thwarted in its quest for an operating license because the state 
and local governments refused to participate in emergency planning 
contending that area around the plant could not be safely evacuated 
in the event of a nuclear emergency 
in late 1987 the nrc changed its rules to allow utilities to 
prepare their own evacuation plans assuming that in the event of a 
real emergency state and local governments would live up to their 
responsibilities and participate nrc finally removed lilcos last 
obstacles to a license the state and local governments by 
dismissing them as legal intervenors before the nrc 
</TEXT>
